Preheat your #oven{} to 200°C. Bring a large #saucepan{} of water to the boil with @salt{1/2%tsp} for the pasta. Halve, peel and chop the @red onion{1}(chopped into small pieces). Grate the @mature cheddar cheese{90%g}.

When boiling, add the @penne pasta{180%g} to the water and bring back to the boil. Cook until tender, ~{12%minutes}. Pop the @baby spinach{100%g} into a #colander{} in your sink. Once the pasta is cooked, drain it over the spinach so it's wilted and piping hot. Set aside.

> TIP: Drizzle with oil to prevent it from sticking.

Meanwhile, heat a drizzle of @oil{1%tsp} in a #frying pan{} on medium-high heat. Once hot, add the @British smoked bacon lardons{60%g} and stir-fry until lightly browned, ~{1-2%minutes}. Pour the bacon and its fat into a #medium bowl{}. Mix in the @panko breadcrumbs{25%g} and @olive oil{1%tbsp} for the crumb, season with @salt{} and @black pepper{}, then stir to combine. Set aside.

> IMPORTANT: Cook bacon thoroughly.

Put your frying pan back on medium-high heat. Add the @olive oil{1%tsp} for the onion and the onion. Stir-fry until the onion is soft, ~{3-4%minutes}, then stir in the @plain flour{8%g}. Cook until it forms a paste consistency, ~{1-2%minutes}. Gradually, stir in the @water{200%ml} and the @chicken stock paste{10%g}. Bring to the boil, stirring continuously, reduce the heat slightly and add the @Italian style herbs{1%tsp}, then stir and simmer until thickened, ~{1-2%minutes}. Mix in the @creme fraiche{150%g}, then remove from the heat.

Add the Cheddar cheese to the sauce and stir until melted. Taste and season with @salt{} and @black pepper{} if needed. Stir the cooked pasta and spinach into the sauce until combined. Pour the pasta into an #ovenproof dish{}, then sprinkle the bacon crumb evenly over the top. Bake on the top shelf of your oven until golden, ~{8-10%minutes}.

When everything is nearly ready, wash up the breadcrumb bowl and pop in the @balsamic vinegar{12%ml} and @olive oil{1%tsp} for the dressing. Season with @salt{} and @black pepper{}. Mix together, then add the @wild rocket{40%g} and toss to coat. Serve the penne in #bowls{} with the salad alongside. Enjoy!